UID:f3d6fb81999963a5@fed-cfpb-news.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260705T190803Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251121
SUMMARY:[Federal Practice Areas] CFPB’s Supervision Division Releases Ne
 w 'Humility Pledge'
DESCRIPTION:Washington\, D.C.—Today\, the CFPB made changes to how the S
 upervision Division conducts exams. Previously\, under the leadership of D
 irector Chopra and Biden’s Director of Supervision Lorelei Salas\, a for
 mer Soros activist who was put on leave in February 2025\, this division w
 as the weaponized arm of the CFPB.\nhttps://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-
 us/newsroom/cfpb-supervision-division-releases-new-humility-pledge/
URL:https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-supervision-div
 ision-releases-new-humility-pledge/
CATEGORIES:Federal Practice Areas
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
